CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 9, 1953 pg. 16, reads: "Visit Art Exhibit - Visiting the National Scholastic Art Exhibition of High School Students this week at Carnegie Art Museum were Mrs. Lillian R. Webb, art specialist of Baltimore, Md.; Miss Elsie Mae Davis, art instructor of Garnet High School, Charleston, W. Va., and Mrs. Lillian B. Reid, art helping teacher of Baltimore, Md. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Lillian R. Webb, Elsie Mae Davis, and Lillian B. Reid looking at the National Scholastic Art Exhibition of High School Students at Carnegie Museum of Art
